gomodel:SYNGO_2992  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.6: \"Electron micrograph of DISC1 immunoreactivity in the neuropil in Brodmann Area 9\"\n- \"The mostcommon configuration was an unlabeled AT forming anasymmetric synapse with a spine that had immunoreac-tivity deposited on the PSD and throughout the spine.\"\n- \"Labeled ATs formed synapses with labeled spines and dendrites; insome of these, only the PSD of the postsynaptic structurewas labeled. Immunolabeled ATs formed asymmetric andsymmetric synapses with equal frequency\"\n\nNote: AT means axon terminal (presynapse).. Experimental description: - \"DISC1 Immunoreactivity at the Lightand Ultrastructural Level in the HumanNeocortex\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2018-03-23" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2992" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_9606" .

